cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about named entity recognition (NER) on French tweets, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also leverages unsupervised learning and uses embeddings, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and deep learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category since the paper uses a CRF model, which is a type of neural network.
